snippet: Dennis Rodman told TMZ that he planned to return to North Korea on Aug. 1 to try to free Kenneth Bae, a Korean-American sentenced to 15 years of hard labor.
abstract: Dennis Rodman tells celebrity news Web site TMZ that he plans to return to North Korea to try to free Kenneth Bae, Korean-American sentenced to 15 years of hard labor on charges of committing crimes against country.

byline.contributor: Choe Sang-hun contributed reporting from Seoul, South Korea.

lead_paragraph: Dennis Rodman told TMZ that he planned to return to North Korea on Aug. 1 to try to free Kenneth Bae, a Korean-American sentenced to 15 years of hard labor.

headline.seo: Rodman Plans New North Korea Trip to Free American
headline.main: Rodman Says He’ll Ask North Korea to Free American
headline.print_headline: Rodman to Ask North Korea to Free American
